re likely to be bored than challenged in school, so if he follows suit I think he will be fine academically. However on the other hand I worry about how academic Kindergarten has become. I want him to have plenty of time to run and play, I fear chaining him to a desk too early will make him miserable. I know he is still a toddler and a ton will change in the next 4 years but he is the classic “all boy” already, constantly go go go, climbing, running ect even more so than the other kids we know his age. I think ideally I’d like to get him into a play based, maybe Montessori type school , but I don’t know if I’ll be able to afford it. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="945" language="en" documentId="5388" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Anna W" date="March 7, 2013 at 9:55 am" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://blogs.babycenter.com/mom_stories/03072013-the-big-kindergarten-question-to-redshirt-or-not/" topic="redshirting" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="5388" notes="" title="The big kindergarten question: To redshirt or not?"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="945"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39"/></xmi:XMI>